# Keep the stdio entrypoint Unix-LF even when cloned on Windows / WSL.
# Without this, CRLF line endings sneak in via git's autocrlf and the
# shebang line (`#!/usr/bin/env python3\r`) makes the kernel look for
# an interpreter named `python3\r`, which fails with a confusing
# "No such file or directory".
#
# Git does not express the executable bit via `.gitattributes` — the
# exec bit was set at the original `git add` time, so cloners who
# preserve `core.fileMode` get it automatically. On filesystems that
# strip the bit (Windows without WSL), run `chmod +x main.py` after
# clone. See README for details.
main.py text eol=lf
